    <text id="R14697444T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Union General Christopher Auger reports in April, 1865, that Confederate General
                    George Pickett's Division was seen moving through Staunton to fight in the
                    Valley.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    HDQRS. DEPARTMENT OF WASHINGTON, TWENTY-SECOND ARMY CORPS,
                    <name type="recipient">Maj.-Gen. HANCOCK,<lb/> Cmdg. Middle Military Division,
                        Winchester:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-04-01">April 1, 1865</date>--<time>8.45 p.m.</time>
                        <name type="place">Washington, D. C.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Gen. Gamble, commanding at Fairfax Court-House, reports that a rebel deserter
                    just arrived there states that Pickett's division passed through Staunton on
                    Monday last to join Early in the Valley.</p>
                <p>I send the report for your consideration. I will have the deserter sent in here
                    in the morning and get his story in full.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>C. C. AUGUR,<lb/> Maj.-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
